# Shell Script Conventions

- Always save shell scripts in the `bin/` folder with a `.sh` extension.
- Always name shell scripts using kebab-case (lowercase words separated by hyphens).

## Examples

```
✅ bin/open-org.sh
✅ bin/run-apex.sh
✅ bin/deploy-metadata.sh

❌ bin/openOrg.sh        (camelCase)
❌ bin/open_org.sh       (snake_case)
❌ bin/OpenOrg.sh        (PascalCase)
❌ scripts/open-org.sh   (wrong folder)
```
